headline: This company’s CEO made 6,666 more than its typical worker
summary: The pay gap between America’s corporate leaders and their workers grew even larger in 2024, according to the AFL-CIO’s annual Executive Paywatch report, released Wednesday.

headline: Dave Ramsey Says He Tips Well, But Draws The Line At The iPad Spin. He Calls It A Guilt Trip That's 'Nickel-And-Diming You To Death'

headline: This coffee chain overtook Starbucks in China. Now it’s open in the US
summary: Chinese brands like Luckin Coffee, Pop Mart, and HEYTEA are expanding in the United States, despite the ongoing trade war. CNN’s Vanessa Yurkevich and Marc Stewart report from two different continents on why the companies covet American customers.

headline: Starbucks Opens Free Study Rooms in China to Lure Customers
